<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/893974-why-is-hella-long">why is hella long?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_893974'><a id="like_count_community_question_893974" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/893974?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F14362.Bless_Me_Ultima">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/893974-why-is-hella-long">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/893974-why-is-hella-long">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10532531-tracy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1430282190i/10532531._UY100_CR38,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10532531-tracy">Tracy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">At our house, we see long books as a good thing - if the story is great, you don&apos;t want it to end. It&apos;d like a tv show with 1 hour episodes versus 1/2<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">At our house, we see long books as a good thing - if the story is great, you don't want it to end. It'd like a tv show with 1 hour episodes versus 1/2 hour episodes. If you love the show - you want the whole hour. So in reality - longer books give you more time to live in the world the author is creating for you. Escape to this other world and enjoy the experience. And if you are not sure what to read next - this is a great place to ask! Tell us what you enjoy and we will give you suggestions. Good books are one of life's greatest gifts.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
